Implement the public `get/2` function.

`get(name, key)` looks up `key` in the cache identified by `name` and returns
`{:ok, value}` on a hit or `:miss` when the key is absent. To keep reads fast,
consult the `<name>_data` ETS table directly with `:ets.lookup/2` instead of
going through the GenServer. The stored value shape is `{value, frequency, seq}`;
match on it to extract the `value`. A successful lookup counts as one access, so
before returning `{:ok, value}` you must bump the entry's frequency by calling
